ransactions flagged only by risk model. Unit test with all four combinations directly catches this. No need for higher-level infrastructure.","test_description":"Mock both models with controlled outputs. Test all four combinations: (scoring_flag=true, risk_flag=false), (true, true), (false, true), (false, false). Verify 'hold for review' decision is true for first three cases, false for fourth. Verify the implementation uses OR, not AND.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Combined output includes both numeric risk score and fraud probability so reviewer can see which model flagged the transaction and why","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Output structure is a data assembly concern, testable at Unit level. Mock both models with known values, call the service, and inspect the response. Real failures: missing field, wrong field name, wrong type, incorrect value propagation. Unit test directly verifies output shape and content. No Integration or higher-level infrastructure needed.","test_description":"Mock scoring model to return risk_score=75, risk model to return fraud_probability=0.92. Call combined service. Verify output JSON/object includes both 'risk_score': 75 and 'fraud_probability': 0.92 as distinct fields with correct values and types.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.98,"Integration":0.01,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13475,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13475},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"196921a9-94df-43c8-a242-638a032e5ef2","uuid":"c82ba821-2f51-49a5-876c-c432b8a7244e"}
